The article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring November 2012 as National Adoption Month. In the proclamation, Obama emphasizes the importance of ensuring that every child has the opportunity to grow up in a permanent and loving family. He acknowledges the contributions of adoptive parents and encourages the elimination of discriminatory barriers to adoption. The proclamation also highlights the efforts of the administration to support adoptive families and improve child outcomes. Obama calls on Americans to observe the month by finding permanent and caring families for children in need and supporting the families who care for them.